
The wee script "Make_all" will concatenate all the Python code into one
file called "all.py"

It can be run as:

    python < all.py

or

    python all.py

or by starting python and then "from all import *"

By default it creates a PDF file called "NooneCurves_python.pdf"

but this plotting is all pretty slopy. It needs a more skilled person.

